Annulus inlet (with swirl)
==========================

Demonstrates the syntheticTurbulenceInlet on an annular cross-section
with a constant area-averaged mean speed and a non-zero swirl
component (swirlNr = 0.5).

Geometry            Annulus (two-block O-grid).
Inlet target        Umean = 10 m/s.
Swirl number        swirlNr = 0.5 (added tangential velocity).
Friction velocity   Auto-computed from the bulk Reynolds number
                    (smooth-pipe correlation).
Solver              foamRun, incompressibleFluid.

Run with:           ./Allrun
Clean with:         ./Allclean

Notes
-----
The mesh in this tutorial is intentionally coarse so the case starts
quickly. Increase nx/ny/nz in system/blockMeshDict and bump endTime in
system/controlDict for a converged statistical run.
